Goal Description
Show key career stats beside the active player on the projector screen with minimal latency, while integrating players_career_stats.csv safely into Firebase.

Confirmed Context
- Projector screen file is: src/pages/viewer/ProjectorScreen.jsx
- Priority is performance (reduce lag) over optional infrastructure changes
- Uploading to Firebase is acceptable and preferred for runtime speed

Proposed Integration Strategy
Do NOT parse stats CSV on the projector/frontend during live auction. Instead, ingest once in AdminPlayers and persist structured stats into each player record in Firebase. Projector then reads already-linked stats with normal realtime data, avoiding heavy parsing/matching work during live display.

Proposed Changes
1. Data Integration (Admin Panel)
[MODIFY] src/pages/admin/AdminPlayers.jsx
- Add an "Upload Career Stats CSV" control.
- Implement handleStatsUpload with PapaParse and batched Firebase updates.
- Save curated fields under player.stats (e.g., batting + bowling blocks + source metadata).
- Show upload summary: matched, ambiguous, unmatched, updated.

2. Matching Logic (Handle same first names safely)
[NEW] deterministic multi-step matcher (no first-name-only match)
- Step 1 (exact): normalize(full_name_from_csv) == normalize(player.player_name)
- Step 2 (strict fallback): if CSV has aliases/clean names, compare normalized aliases to normalized full player name.
- Step 3 (disambiguation keys): when multiple players share same normalized token, require at least one secondary key match (group, age, team/history field if available in CSV).
- Step 4 (ambiguous bucket): if still multiple matches, do not auto-write; log as ambiguous for manual mapping.
- Step 5 (unmatched bucket): log rows with no confident match.

Important rule:
- Never auto-assign stats using first name alone (e.g., multiple "Aarya" entries).

3. Projector UI + Performance
[MODIFY] src/pages/viewer/ProjectorScreen.jsx
- Add compact stats panel near current player card (batting/bowling highlights).
- Render only small, precomputed display fields from player.stats (no expensive transforms in render path).
- Memoize derived display values; avoid sorting/filtering work on every tick where possible.
- Keep image fallback lightweight and avoid extra animation complexity that can drop frames.

Lag Reduction Plan (Primary Concern)
- Pre-ingest stats into Firebase once (major win).
- Keep projector payload slim: only fields needed for live display in player.stats.
- Avoid client-side CSV parsing or fuzzy search during auction runtime.
- Batch admin writes to reduce network chatter.
- For ambiguous matches, require manual resolution upfront rather than runtime guessing.

Verification Plan
- Upload career stats CSV from AdminPlayers and confirm:
  - Correct players get stats
  - Ambiguous/unmatched rows are reported, not silently assigned
- Open projector screen and verify:
  - Stats panel appears for current player
  - Missing stats degrades gracefully
  - Live transitions remain smooth without added lag spikes
